Now that I have the structure of both sheets, I can create the INDEX&MATCH formulas to fill the yellow cells in the Task sheet.

```json
{
  "analysis": "I have the structure of both sheets. The Data sheet has the series codes in column B, countries in column C, and years in columns H-L. The Task sheet has the countries in column C and years in row 9. I can create INDEX&MATCH formulas to fill the yellow cells.",
  "plan": "I'll create INDEX&MATCH formulas for each section of yellow cells in the Task sheet. For example, for cell H12, the formula will be =INDEX(Data!H:L,MATCH(1,(Data!B:B=D12)*(Data!C:C=C12)*(Data!9:9=H9),0))",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "python3 << 'EOF'
from openpyxl import load_workbook

file_path = 'gdp.xlsx'
wb = load_workbook(file_path, data_only=False)
task_ws = wb['Task']
data_ws = wb['Data']

# Fill exports data (H12:L17)
for row in range(12, 18):
    for col in range(8, 13):
        task_ws.cell(row, col).value = f"=INDEX(Data!{chr(72+col-8)}:{chr(76+col-8)},MATCH(1,(Data!B:B=Task!D{row})*(Data!C:C=Task!C{row})*(Data!9:9=Task!{chr(72+col-8)}9),0))"

# Fill imports data (H19:L24)
for row in range(19, 25):
    for col in range(8, 13):
        task_ws.cell(row, col).value = f"=INDEX(Data!{chr(72+col-8)}:{chr(76+col-8)},MATCH(1,(Data!B:B=Task!D{row})*(Data!C:C=Task!C{row})*(Data!9:9=Task!{chr(72+col-8)}9),0))"

# Fill GDP data (H26:L31)
for row in range(26, 32):
    for col in range(8, 13):
        task_ws.cell(row, col).value = f"=INDEX(Data!{chr(72+col-8)}:{chr(76+col-8)},MATCH(1,(Data!B:B=Task!D{row})*(Data!C:C=Task!C{row})*(Data!9:9=Task!{chr(72+col-8)}9),0))"

wb.save('gdp.xlsx')
EOF
",
      "duration": 2.0
    }
  ],
  "task_complete": false
}
```
